channel.description: This file is an XML representation of an issue

item.title: [HIVE-22824] JoinProjectTranspose rule should skip Projects containing windowing expression
item.description: Otherwise this rule could end up creating plan with windowing expression within join condition which hive doesn't know how to process.
item.summary: JoinProjectTranspose rule should skip Projects containing windowing expression

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

A couple of comments:

  • Can we add a test case for the issue? Currently the following seems to fail: 
    CREATE TABLE table1 (a INT, b INT);
INSERT INTO table1 VALUES (1, 2), (1, 2), (1, 2), (1, 2);

EXPLAIN CBO
SELECT sub1.r FROM
(
        SELECT
            RANK() OVER (ORDER BY t1.b desc) as r
        FROM table1 t1
        JOIN table1 t2 ON t1.a = t2.b
) sub1
LEFT OUTER JOIN table1 t3
ON sub1.r = t3.a;
  • Can we create a Calcite issue and contribute the fix? iiuc, this issue can lead to incorrect rewriting, and thus, results. Further, please create a Hive issue / leave a note to remove the logic in Hive's JoinProjectTransposeRule once we upgrade?
jcamachorodriguez Added the test and TODO in latest change. Also opened CALCITE-3824
